    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="459"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d459">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">J.C.S.</gloss> Files</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the British Chiefs of Staff</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d459fn1">For the action taken on this paper at the 115th
                        Meeting of the Combined Chiefs of Staff, August 23, 1943, see <hi
                            rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_939">p. 939</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">most secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 246/1</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quebec</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-21">21 August
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Movement of the “Queens”</hi>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d459fn2">i.e., the requisitioned passenger liners <hi
                            rend="italic">Queen Elizabeth</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Queen
                            Mary.</hi>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <p>At the 94th Meeting of the Combined Chiefs of Staff during the <gloss
                        target="#t_Trident1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Trident</hi>
                    </gloss> Conference,<note n="3" xml:id="d459fn3">See <hi rend="italic"
                        >ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_179">p. 179</ref>.</note> approval was given to
                    the “<hi rend="italic">Queens</hi>” running on <pb facs="1156" n="1042"
                        xml:id="pg_1042"/> a 28 day cycle as at that time the urgency of lifting
                    personnel was not as great as it is now.</p>
                <p>It is understood that a situation is developing in which it is essential to lift
                    as many personnel as possible, and in view of the longer nights we recommend
                    that the Combined Chiefs of Staff should now approve that the “<hi rend="italic"
                        >Queens</hi>” should revert to running on a 21 day cycle.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
